<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99199947763849></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99199947763849><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99199947763849>RE: what ARE bane spells?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99199947763849#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=31822><span id=Scholar>Aline</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>39 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 8th 7:24 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, Bane Spells are level 60 Wizard Spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;They are suppose to make wizards more used in raids.  The first Bane Spell: Porlo's Fury, deals 2000 damage to Yelinak Dragons.  The second Bane Spell: Hsagra's Wrath, deals 2000 damage to Tormax Giants.<br><br>And YES, Ice Comet IS worth it.  If you haven't gotten Staff of the Wheel yet, here is the walkthrough for Graffe.com:<br><br>. Azia- In Erud's crossing on the deep part of the ocean floor past the shipwreck infested with undead, location -1162, +2340 (one user suggested levitating to find the coordinates first, then diving for it). Use the best of your shields, load your fades, shadow steps and gates. Acquiring this rod can get ugly. Seems that 'Killer Sharks' (level 40) inhabit this area and make it very difficult to acquire the rods. Some say the sharks see through invisible and some say they cannot. - you have been warned - For even more help on this rod, I suggest looking at this walkthru and also reading this text file.<br><br>2. Beza- In Everfrost, within the underwater caves, it is in the "house" all the way back and right in the cave, where three Ice boned skeletons guard it in the center of the room. To find the hole in the ice that leads to the underwater cave, goto +2420, -4060. You may or may not need enduring breath for this swim depending on your swimming skill. Jump in the water and swim North. Once you hit dry land inside the cave, keep right the whole way until you reach the "house". (mob info correction by Talisin Sa`Lidar)<br><br>3. Caza- Lake Rathe, Underneath the first island you see is an underwater tunnel leading to a stone tower, its on the top floor of the tower (need enduring breath for this one). This is guarded by water goblins that may attack unprovoked. Be careful for some say they can see through invisiblitly also. - you have been warned - <br><br>4. Dena- Dagnor's Cauldron, right outside the entrance to Kedge Keep. If you face with your back to Kedge Keep, it is directly diagonal left, in a corner. Loc -890, -740.<br><br>5. Ena- Lower Guk in the Reanimated hand room. This one is the only one you need a group for, unless you are brave and kamakaze it. Warning: depending on how your video card / colors are set up, the floor may be the same color as the rod in this room and it makes it very hard to find with the Hand and the dar beating on you. <br><br>6. Fana- Oasis is correct but the tower is underwater next to the above ground tower, this one is on the top floor of the tower as well. This is guarded by water goblins that may attack unprovoked. Be careful for some say they can see through invisiblitly also. - you have been warned - <br><br>7. Geza- Highpass Hold is correct, it is in the water near the waterfall closest to the Tiger's Roar Inn, there are two waterfalls there, the rod is in front of the one closest to the Inn.<br><br>8. Heda- Erudin is wrong, it is within the Qeynos Aqueducts, in the shark pit there. Some High Elves with the wrong faction may have to deal with an NPC by the name of Riggin Vix, in which they may be KoS to.<br><br>9. Izah- Neriak is correct, but it is in the water in front of the bar called "The Blind Fish". The bar has four glass windows that are underwater and the rod spawns right in front of those windows. (If you do not know Neriak or are not welcomed there, I suggest creating a newbie Dark Elf to get familiar with the waterway area, the guards, and the location of the rod before attempting to grab this one. There are MANY guards that patrol the bridge area but you will be safe in the water - Graffë)<br><br>10. Jaka- It is in Unrest but not near a mob that drops dwarven armor. It is in the water outside to the right of the mansion. Near where the the Gnome Spelunker is. Instead of going into the tunnel that leads to the Spelunker, there is a very shallow tunnel that is to the right. Within that tunnel lies the rod.<br><br>Once you have all the rods, ask Sulgar for a chest.  Put all the rods into the chest and hit combine.  You should get Staff of the Wheel and Star of Eye.  If you want the Ice Comet spell, you turn both the items back in for the Runes which are both no drop.  <br><br>The easier way to get Ice Comet is to buy it in your local Mart (Gfay or Ecommon)<br><br>Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aline Griffonfeather of Povar<br>Erudite Evoker</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
